1
00:00:00,848 --> 00:00:02,127
Previously on "Lost"...

2
00:00:02,264 --> 00:00:03,925
We're gonna have
to take the boy.

3
00:00:04,064 --> 00:00:05,724
I'm not giving you anybody!

4
00:00:05,817 --> 00:00:08,478
- Dad! Dad!
- Walt!

5
00:00:14,972 --> 00:00:16,440
Where is she?

6
00:00:16,795 --> 00:00:19,599
- You mean Kate?
- I love her.

7
00:00:33,803 --> 00:00:38,182
Kate! Kate!

8
00:00:42,574 --> 00:00:44,567
Look here and here.

9
00:00:44,660 --> 00:00:48,323
You can see it's eroding up the
spinal artery in the l5 area.

10
00:00:48,464 --> 00:00:51,442
Plus all this
extradural growth--

11
00:00:51,670 --> 00:00:54,177
I'm surprised it hasn't
caused permanent ischemia.

12
00:00:58,612 --> 00:01:01,082
He says you don't need
to talk in whispers.

13
00:01:01,176 --> 00:01:03,175
He knows he doesn't
have a chance.

14
00:01:04,009 --> 00:01:05,908
Your father appreciates candor.

15
00:01:05,954 --> 00:01:07,329
We both do.

16
00:01:08,635 --> 00:01:11,297
Well, then tell
him I'm very sorry,

17
00:01:11,390 --> 00:01:13,574
but he's not a
candidate for surgery.

18
00:01:21,196 --> 00:01:25,385
The way the tumor is situated on the
spine, it's just not possible to
remove it.

19
00:01:27,767 --> 00:01:30,955
He wants to know
why you won't try.

20
00:01:31,327 --> 00:01:33,942
Because what your
father is looking for

21
00:01:33,990 --> 00:01:39,607
is not a surgical procedure.
What he is looking for is a miracle.

22
00:01:48,023 --> 00:01:52,306
He said, "I did not come
all this way for you, sir.

23
00:01:52,399 --> 00:01:54,155
I came for him."

24
00:01:59,807 --> 00:02:02,279
Miss Busoni, I, uh--

25
00:02:02,324 --> 00:02:05,178
You fixed a woman with a
crushed spinal column--

26
00:02:05,224 --> 00:02:08,601
an impossible surgery.
And now she walks, yes?

27
00:02:08,695 --> 00:02:11,753
I consulted many medical journals
before making this trip here.

28
00:02:11,783 --> 00:02:14,174
Then you should know it
was a very different case

29
00:02:14,204 --> 00:02:16,342
under very
different circumstances.

30
00:02:16,482 --> 00:02:18,571
But a miracle, right?

31
00:02:21,514 --> 00:02:23,664
Look, everything that
my father is saying--

32
00:02:23,744 --> 00:02:27,409
the risks, the unlikelihood--
he's absolutely right.

33
00:02:27,501 --> 00:02:29,257
But will you try?

34
00:02:49,817 --> 00:02:52,367
I'll have to admit him in
the next couple of weeks,

35
00:02:52,519 --> 00:02:54,371
run some tests.

36
00:03:39,882 --> 00:03:40,684
Locke?

37
00:03:47,598 --> 00:03:48,256
John!

38
00:03:51,563 --> 00:03:55,037
- Stay in there. Stay--
- - Michael! What are you--

39
00:03:55,131 --> 00:03:59,033
- Stay in there, Jack!
- Hey, whatever's going on--

40
00:03:59,126 --> 00:04:00,543
Look, I'm going after my son.

41
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:04,237
I'm going after my son,
and nobody is going to stop me, okay?

42
00:04:04,330 --> 00:04:07,092
Okay? That is my right.
That is a father's right.

43
00:04:07,179 --> 00:04:08,473
There's another way
to go about this--

44
00:04:08,503 --> 00:04:11,203
- Get in the damn room!
- You gonna shoot me, Michael?!

45
00:04:13,032 --> 00:04:16,460
No. But I'll shoot
your damn computer.

46
00:04:16,690 --> 00:04:19,238
That thing is not what
you think it is anyway.

47
00:04:19,330 --> 00:04:23,615
You don't understand, man. You don't
have any idea. Now get in there!

48
00:04:23,708 --> 00:04:25,366
Michael! Michael, listen,

49
00:04:25,506 --> 00:04:28,006
we can do this together, okay?
I'll come with you.

50
00:04:28,022 --> 00:04:30,828
No. I have to do it... now.

51
00:04:31,535 --> 00:04:34,093
I have to do it alone.

52
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:56,491
What happened?

53
00:04:56,611 --> 00:04:58,422
Michael knocked you out.

54
00:04:58,835 --> 00:04:59,969
Look over here.

55
00:05:00,062 --> 00:05:02,580
- Why would he...
- He went after Walt.

56
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:05,842
You feel nauseated? Sick?

57
00:05:06,122 --> 00:05:08,499
No, I'm okay.

58
00:05:08,683 --> 00:05:11,445
Good. Give me a boost up.

59
00:05:13,691 --> 00:05:17,681
It's no use.
I bolted it shut from the inside.

60
00:05:17,675 --> 00:05:18,764
You did what?

61
00:05:18,995 --> 00:05:24,185
No point in changing the combination if
you can get in through the air vent.

62
00:05:24,839 --> 00:05:26,880
That's really good
thinking, John.

63
00:05:29,384 --> 00:05:31,784
You want to tell me why
you let Michael in here?

64
00:05:31,804 --> 00:05:34,466
Uh, he... he wanted a gun.

65
00:05:35,492 --> 00:05:37,252
For shooting practice.

66
00:05:38,227 --> 00:05:39,704
Shooting practice.

67
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:44,243
The button.

68
00:05:47,662 --> 00:05:51,127
- How long was I out?
- About 20 minutes.

69
00:05:52,434 --> 00:05:55,253
We're on shift for the next four hours.
There's nobody coming down here.

70
00:05:55,283 --> 00:06:00,235
Yeah, I know. We better hope Sawyer
shows up to get his band-aid changed.

71
00:06:15,402 --> 00:06:16,680
Mornin'.

72
00:06:17,618 --> 00:06:19,417
Did you just throw
a banana at me?

73
00:06:19,398 --> 00:06:21,011
Couldn't find any rocks.

74
00:06:23,018 --> 00:06:26,015
There are nicer ways to
wake a man up, Freckles.

75
00:06:26,603 --> 00:06:28,994
Come on. It's time to go
get your bandages changed.

76
00:06:29,024 --> 00:06:30,922
Well, why can't
you do it for me?

77
00:06:31,019 --> 00:06:34,824
Because I'm not your nurse,
and Jack's got the bandages.

78
00:06:35,574 --> 00:06:37,277
Of course he does.

79
00:06:42,183 --> 00:06:43,747
You want to give me a hand?

80
00:06:54,026 --> 00:06:54,972
Thanks.

81
00:06:57,737 --> 00:06:58,720
Come on.

82
00:07:02,142 --> 00:07:03,933
This place still creeps me out.

83
00:07:04,212 --> 00:07:05,586
You'll get used to it.

84
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:08,367
Where is everybody?

85
00:07:09,767 --> 00:07:11,906
Jack? John?

86
00:07:12,502 --> 00:07:14,255
Maybe they went
out for ice cream.

87
00:07:14,443 --> 00:07:15,141
Shh.

88
00:07:16,506 --> 00:07:19,014
- In here! Hey!
- Jack?

89
00:07:19,106 --> 00:07:20,481
In here! In the armory!

90
00:07:20,574 --> 00:07:22,150
Michael locked us in here!

91
00:07:22,277 --> 00:07:24,558
- What did he say?
- I got it.

92
00:07:27,734 --> 00:07:29,927
Hope you got the combo, doc.

93
00:07:30,061 --> 00:07:33,245
Right 3 times to 25.

94
00:07:33,928 --> 00:07:35,164
25, got it.

95
00:07:35,351 --> 00:07:37,624
Left 2 times to 29.

96
00:07:40,572 --> 00:07:42,656
Right once to 40.

97
00:07:47,424 --> 00:07:48,844
Howdy, boys.

98
00:07:49,123 --> 00:07:52,214
- What are you doing, Jack?
- We're going after him.

99
00:07:55,822 --> 00:07:58,522
Hey, what... what happened?

100
00:07:58,618 --> 00:08:00,371
Michael went after Walt.

101
00:08:01,736 --> 00:08:03,195
Went after Walt?

102
00:08:03,340 --> 00:08:08,124
Pulled a gun on me, put us both
in there and went after Walt.

103
00:08:11,347 --> 00:08:13,927
Hey.  What are you doing?

104
00:08:14,571 --> 00:08:17,611
What does it look like?
Comin' with ya.

105
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:19,266
You're still on antibiotics.

106
00:08:19,452 --> 00:08:22,125
It's a good thing I'm
traveling with my doctor then.

107
00:08:33,142 --> 00:08:34,193
How  is he?

108
00:08:35,049 --> 00:08:36,854
Thought you'd gone home.

109
00:08:36,992 --> 00:08:39,242
My home is a hotel room.

110
00:08:41,808 --> 00:08:43,502
I like it more here.

111
00:08:45,241 --> 00:08:47,319
Think you need to
find a better hotel.

112
00:08:48,023 --> 00:08:50,215
You didn't answer my question.

113
00:08:53,286 --> 00:08:55,616
His counts aren't where
I'd like 'em to be.

114
00:08:57,577 --> 00:09:00,670
You've been doing tests
for a month now, Jack.

115
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:02,741
I'm thorough.

116
00:09:15,172 --> 00:09:17,548
I have a confession to make.

117
00:09:19,976 --> 00:09:22,163
I don't believe in miracles.

118
00:09:22,921 --> 00:09:26,382
Yeah. Guess I'm not too
sure about them, either.

119
00:09:27,363 --> 00:09:30,504
I bet your wife
feels differently.

120
00:09:32,183 --> 00:09:36,421
Your wife.
She's the woman you fixed, isn't she?

121
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:37,358
Yes.

122
00:09:40,214 --> 00:09:42,211
I'm thorough, too.

123
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:49,076
She must be a very special person to
let you work until 4:30 in the morning.

124
00:09:51,038 --> 00:09:52,936
I completely lost track...

125
00:09:53,636 --> 00:09:55,726
I've gotta--
will you excuse me?

126
00:09:55,818 --> 00:09:57,574
Yes, of course. Go.

127
00:09:59,824 --> 00:10:01,381
Jack?

128
00:10:02,174 --> 00:10:03,738
Thank you.

129
00:10:04,814 --> 00:10:07,141
Yeah. Of course.

130
00:10:08,495 --> 00:10:10,108
- Good night.
- Good night.

131
00:10:20,403 --> 00:10:21,004
Hey.

132
00:10:24,362 --> 00:10:25,305
How is he?

133
00:10:26,754 --> 00:10:28,990
Hey. Sorry to wake you.

134
00:10:31,090 --> 00:10:33,281
I gotta get up anyway.

135
00:10:35,482 --> 00:10:36,660
So how is he?

136
00:10:38,336 --> 00:10:40,073
About the same.

137
00:10:46,427 --> 00:10:48,098
Sarah, I'm sorry.

138
00:10:48,513 --> 00:10:52,220
I meant to... I just got...

139
00:10:52,361 --> 00:10:58,032
Hey... that's the price of
being a miracle worker.

140
00:11:03,684 --> 00:11:04,684
Where are you going?

141
00:11:04,863 --> 00:11:08,433
I've gotta go to the gym,
and then I've got some papers to grade.

142
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:32,988
I didn't want to say anything
until I knew either way, but, um...

143
00:11:34,248 --> 00:11:37,916
I was late,
so I got a pregnancy test.

144
00:11:46,740 --> 00:11:49,557
Don't worry. It's negative.

145
00:11:54,272 --> 00:11:55,742
Do you, um...

146
00:11:56,356 --> 00:11:58,345
do you want to talk about it?

147
00:11:59,867 --> 00:12:01,317
What's to talk about?

148
00:12:03,255 --> 00:12:05,086
Sarah, I...

149
00:12:05,345 --> 00:12:07,103
See you later, Jack.

150
00:12:16,776 --> 00:12:17,594
Well?

151
00:12:18,977 --> 00:12:21,177
Well, I can't tell you
it's definitely Michael's,

152
00:12:21,207 --> 00:12:23,486
but looks like his boot print.

153
00:12:23,685 --> 00:12:25,525
There's one over here, too.

154
00:12:25,668 --> 00:12:27,945
That sounds like a trail.

155
00:12:28,177 --> 00:12:31,135
- You got a gun for me?
- You're not coming.

156
00:12:31,276 --> 00:12:32,973
- Excuse me?
- You're not coming.

157
00:12:33,068 --> 00:12:35,124
Someone has to be here to
take care of the button.

158
00:12:35,154 --> 00:12:36,754
So why should that
person be me?

159
00:12:36,762 --> 00:12:40,574
- I can track, carry a gun--
- - You're not comin'. You're stayin'.

160
00:12:41,625 --> 00:12:42,401
All right?

161
00:12:48,412 --> 00:12:49,208
Let's go.

162
00:13:07,810 --> 00:13:09,327
What did she do to you?

163
00:13:09,842 --> 00:13:11,932
- What?
- Kate.

164
00:13:12,662 --> 00:13:15,992
- What did she do?
- She didn't do anything.

165
00:13:16,085 --> 00:13:16,987
Right.

166
00:13:17,729 --> 00:13:22,241
You yellin' at her 'cause she wanted to
help get Mike back makes a lot of sense.

167
00:13:22,329 --> 00:13:24,979
Why don't you go back and
see if I hurt her feelings?

168
00:13:25,081 --> 00:13:26,503
I'm just sayin'.

169
00:13:26,608 --> 00:13:30,129
Yeah. I know. You love her.

170
00:13:30,585 --> 00:13:32,391
What did you say?

171
00:13:35,379 --> 00:13:36,133
What?

172
00:13:37,815 --> 00:13:41,241
Does any of this look familiar
from when you were coming back?

173
00:13:41,375 --> 00:13:44,215
Oh, yeah.
There's my favorite leaf.

174
00:13:44,427 --> 00:13:46,160
How could I forget this place?

175
00:13:46,251 --> 00:13:47,341
What's wrong?

176
00:13:47,461 --> 00:13:51,511
When you came across the island,
what side was the ocean on?

177
00:13:59,128 --> 00:14:01,857
You came from the east.
Michael's heading north.

178
00:14:01,931 --> 00:14:03,416
What  the hell's that
supposed to mean?

179
00:14:03,446 --> 00:14:06,155
That means he's not going
back to where you came from.

180
00:14:08,447 --> 00:14:11,107
He's heading somewhere else.

181
00:14:24,709 --> 00:14:26,180
*The sun's very strong today.

182
00:14:26,364 --> 00:14:27,928
*I don't need a hat.

183
00:14:28,441 --> 00:14:29,959
*I know.

184
00:14:31,384 --> 00:14:33,195
*Just wear it.

185
00:14:36,557 --> 00:14:38,409
*I think something's wrong.

186
00:14:43,975 --> 00:14:46,491
- Hello, Hurley.
- Hey.

187
00:14:47,002 --> 00:14:48,710
Cool hat, dude.

188
00:14:51,095 --> 00:14:54,376
- Is Kate all right?
- Uh... yeah.

189
00:14:56,058 --> 00:14:58,447
I guess Michael took off.

190
00:14:58,855 --> 00:15:00,485
*What's he saying?

191
00:15:01,142 --> 00:15:02,782
What do you mean, he took off?

192
00:15:02,921 --> 00:15:05,502
He stole some guns,
and he went all commando.

193
00:15:05,645 --> 00:15:08,004
Said he was going after Walt.

194
00:15:09,077 --> 00:15:11,645
Later, dudes.
Gotta get to the hatch.

195
00:15:18,841 --> 00:15:20,697
*What are you doing?

196
00:15:20,841 --> 00:15:22,456
*He said they just left.

197
00:15:22,493 --> 00:15:24,268
*If I hurry I can catch up...

198
00:15:24,572 --> 00:15:26,200
*You're not going anywhere.

199
00:15:26,564 --> 00:15:27,932
*Don't go!

200
00:15:28,498 --> 00:15:31,075
*Don't walk away from me!

201
00:15:31,992 --> 00:15:34,037
*While you were on that raft...

202
00:15:34,267 --> 00:15:36,549
*do you know how worried I was?

203
00:15:37,295 --> 00:15:40,197
*I didn't know if you
were dead or alive.

204
00:15:40,945 --> 00:15:43,128
*I was out of my head.

205
00:15:44,839 --> 00:15:46,643
*I won't go through taht again.

206
00:15:49,725 --> 00:15:51,906
*Michael's my friend.

207
00:15:54,107 --> 00:15:56,323
*I'm your wife.

208
00:16:17,129 --> 00:16:20,163
Hey, doc. Wanna slow down?

209
00:16:22,686 --> 00:16:24,252
Take a break a minute?

210
00:16:24,999 --> 00:16:25,972
Good idea.

211
00:16:30,108 --> 00:16:31,555
He still heading north?

212
00:16:33,179 --> 00:16:34,228
Yup.

213
00:16:34,678 --> 00:16:36,271
You think he's lost?

214
00:16:36,486 --> 00:16:37,898
Doesn't seem to be.

215
00:16:38,066 --> 00:16:39,966
Trail's as straight
as the interstate.

216
00:16:40,653 --> 00:16:43,110
The path of a man who
knows where he's going.

217
00:16:45,585 --> 00:16:47,439
Where are you going, Jack?

218
00:16:48,942 --> 00:16:50,306
What?

219
00:16:51,051 --> 00:16:53,491
Well, let's say we catch
up with him-- Michael.

220
00:16:53,615 --> 00:16:55,276
What are you gonna do?

221
00:16:56,161 --> 00:16:57,536
I'm gonna bring him back.

222
00:16:57,909 --> 00:16:59,759
What  if he doesn't
want to come back?

223
00:17:00,826 --> 00:17:02,678
I'll talk him into coming back.

224
00:17:03,284 --> 00:17:06,484
This is the second time he's gone
after Walt. He knocked me out.

225
00:17:06,593 --> 00:17:08,444
He locked us both up.

226
00:17:08,582 --> 00:17:12,129
Something tells me he might
be past listening to reason.

227
00:17:12,666 --> 00:17:16,622
What, you think we should just
let him go, write him off?

228
00:17:16,772 --> 00:17:21,595
Who are we to tell anyone
what they can or can't do?

229
00:17:36,130 --> 00:17:38,125
It's not too late to go back.

230
00:17:38,218 --> 00:17:39,401
The tumor's aggressive,

231
00:17:39,543 --> 00:17:43,101
but your father could lead a very
normal life for at least another year.

232
00:17:43,131 --> 00:17:43,911
Go back?

233
00:17:44,048 --> 00:17:46,759
Go back where? Home?

234
00:17:48,535 --> 00:17:50,386
Have you changed
your mind, Jack?

235
00:17:50,478 --> 00:17:53,214
No.  No.

236
00:18:03,424 --> 00:18:04,562
Is that it?

237
00:18:12,208 --> 00:18:17,641
Even if you don't succeed,
you're giving us a chance.

238
00:18:19,142 --> 00:18:20,998
That's all we wanted.

239
00:18:24,653 --> 00:18:27,466
I'll come out and check
on you before I scrub in.

240
00:18:28,773 --> 00:18:29,669
Okay.

241
00:18:34,715 --> 00:18:36,116
Am I interrupting?

242
00:18:37,490 --> 00:18:39,723
No. I was just leaving.

243
00:18:43,603 --> 00:18:45,548
I'll see you in the morning.

244
00:18:46,623 --> 00:18:48,482
I'll see you in the morning.

245
00:18:54,922 --> 00:18:58,873
I.T.R. Reports need to be signed
by you as chief resident.

246
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:05,186
What?

247
00:19:06,447 --> 00:19:08,079
Careful.

248
00:19:10,567 --> 00:19:11,911
There's a line, son.

249
00:19:12,144 --> 00:19:13,341
You know it's there.

250
00:19:13,793 --> 00:19:15,598
And pretending it's not...

251
00:19:16,414 --> 00:19:17,819
that would be a mistake.

252
00:19:21,593 --> 00:19:23,349
Guess you would know.

253
00:19:27,650 --> 00:19:30,675
It may be okay for
some people, Jack,

254
00:19:31,001 --> 00:19:32,757
but not for you.

255
00:20:00,613 --> 00:20:02,758
Sure Mike went this way?

256
00:20:03,459 --> 00:20:04,978
Why do you ask?

257
00:20:05,110 --> 00:20:06,915
Oh, I don't know, Mr. Clean.

258
00:20:07,005 --> 00:20:10,773
I probably would have gone
around Mount Vesuvius.

259
00:20:12,213 --> 00:20:14,361
Why did you pick that name?

260
00:20:16,203 --> 00:20:18,452
Ain't it obvious?

