00:20:18,857 --> 00:20:22,400
All you need's an
earring and a mop.

262
00:20:23,596 --> 00:20:26,829
No, your name.
Why did you pick "Sawyer"?

263
00:20:27,248 --> 00:20:28,838
What do you mean, "pick"?

264
00:20:28,907 --> 00:20:33,241
After the census,
Hurley gave me the flight manifest.

265
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:38,411
Your name is James.
Right? James Ford.

266
00:20:39,109 --> 00:20:41,232
What's it to you?

267
00:20:41,538 --> 00:20:44,508
Just an interesting name to choose,
is all.

268
00:20:44,666 --> 00:20:46,479
Who'd you get it from?

269
00:20:46,574 --> 00:20:49,545
Who says I got it from anybody?

270
00:20:55,878 --> 00:20:58,637
- Michael!
- Jack, get down!

271
00:20:58,778 --> 00:21:02,355
- Michael!
- Jack! Jack!

272
00:21:09,575 --> 00:21:10,397
Michael!

273
00:21:16,002 --> 00:21:17,759
- Michael!
- Jack.

274
00:21:20,235 --> 00:21:21,192
What?

275
00:21:24,085 --> 00:21:25,140
He's close.

276
00:21:25,544 --> 00:21:28,375
Yeah, and if he was shooting at someone,
you want 'em coming back?

277
00:21:28,405 --> 00:21:29,666
Personally, hell, yeah.

278
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:32,054
You said these people were
two days across the island.

279
00:21:32,084 --> 00:21:34,989
Yeah, and they took Cindy less
than a mile from our camp.

280
00:21:35,075 --> 00:21:35,924
Over here.

281
00:21:42,114 --> 00:21:45,485
- Shell casings. How many?
- Three. Michael's.

282
00:21:45,565 --> 00:21:48,465
You boys deaf?
I heard at least seven shots.

283
00:21:48,619 --> 00:21:51,301
You heard 'em, Daniel Boone.
What's your count?

284
00:21:51,441 --> 00:21:53,530
Yeah. Seven sounds about right.

285
00:21:54,371 --> 00:21:56,175
It's gettin' dark.

286
00:21:56,361 --> 00:21:58,356
Which way did Mike go?

287
00:22:10,113 --> 00:22:10,866
What?

288
00:22:11,968 --> 00:22:16,804
You out here for Michael or
just payback for getting shot?

289
00:22:17,827 --> 00:22:20,131
Why are you out here, doc?

290
00:22:22,350 --> 00:22:26,701
You got your reasons,
and I got mine.

291
00:22:38,811 --> 00:22:39,596
Jack.

292
00:22:40,338 --> 00:22:41,307
Jack!

293
00:22:41,421 --> 00:22:42,844
- I had it.
- I know, son.

294
00:22:42,983 --> 00:22:45,360
I got it! I got it all.
I mean, I had it!

295
00:22:45,454 --> 00:22:50,169
He was a sick old man on a table
for seven and a half hours.

296
00:22:50,402 --> 00:22:52,984
His heart gave out.
It's nobody's fault.

297
00:22:57,750 --> 00:22:59,402
Gotta go tell her.

298
00:23:00,218 --> 00:23:02,488
Yeah, well,
I've already done that.

299
00:23:06,255 --> 00:23:10,364
Lest you forget,
I am still chief of surgery.

300
00:23:13,488 --> 00:23:14,617
Where is she?

301
00:23:16,439 --> 00:23:19,137
- Maybe you should go home.
- Where is she?

302
00:23:21,128 --> 00:23:22,560
She's gone.

303
00:23:27,767 --> 00:23:28,807
Jack...

304
00:23:30,192 --> 00:23:31,277
go home.

305
00:23:56,517 --> 00:23:57,277
Jack?

306
00:24:01,197 --> 00:24:02,316
Gabriela.

307
00:24:07,870 --> 00:24:10,464
My father told me that you'd gone.
I, uh...

308
00:24:14,503 --> 00:24:16,807
- I, uh...
- Thank you.

309
00:24:17,578 --> 00:24:19,569
Thank you for trying.

310
00:24:25,439 --> 00:24:29,744
Gabriela... I'm so sorry.

311
00:24:36,897 --> 00:24:42,787
I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry that I couldn't...

312
00:24:51,442 --> 00:24:53,973
- Wha...
- It's okay.

313
00:24:56,144 --> 00:24:57,517
I...

314
00:24:58,841 --> 00:24:59,764
I'm...

315
00:25:04,039 --> 00:25:05,255
I can't.

316
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:19,190
What do you mean, you lost it?

317
00:25:19,312 --> 00:25:21,264
He's a man, not a boar.

318
00:25:21,403 --> 00:25:23,968
The signs' more subtle.
I need light to follow.

319
00:25:24,113 --> 00:25:24,707
Here.

320
00:25:25,819 --> 00:25:26,688
Light.

321
00:25:30,239 --> 00:25:31,900
I think we'd better head back.

322
00:25:32,041 --> 00:25:32,512
What?

323
00:25:32,649 --> 00:25:34,610
- Just find the trail, John.
- I've lost the trail.

324
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:36,492
You don't just lose a trail.

325
00:25:36,584 --> 00:25:38,499
You just don't
want to find him.

326
00:25:38,670 --> 00:25:40,282
Yeah, that's right, Jack.

327
00:25:40,422 --> 00:25:41,859
I've been running
through the jungle

328
00:25:41,889 --> 00:25:45,125
toward the sound of gunfire
because I don't care about Michael.

329
00:25:45,543 --> 00:25:48,095
Don't turn around on me, John.

330
00:25:48,188 --> 00:25:50,101
You're not gonna get him to come back,
and you know it!

331
00:25:50,131 --> 00:25:52,716
You know what happens if we
just turn around and go back?

332
00:25:52,746 --> 00:25:54,700
We're never gonna
see him again,

333
00:25:54,846 --> 00:25:56,349
and that's gonna be on us--

334
00:25:56,509 --> 00:25:59,469
on you and on me.

335
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:02,958
You're exactly right, Jack!

336
00:26:05,052 --> 00:26:07,043
But if I were you,

337
00:26:07,411 --> 00:26:10,599
I'd listen to Mr. Locke.

338
00:26:22,403 --> 00:26:23,659
Who are you?

339
00:26:23,907 --> 00:26:27,153
He's the son of a bitch
who shot me on the raft.

340
00:26:27,557 --> 00:26:29,904
Why don't you
point the gun down?

341
00:26:30,396 --> 00:26:31,250
Ow!

342
00:26:40,270 --> 00:26:44,707
Probably be best if we just keep
our hands at our sides, gentlemen.

343
00:26:45,331 --> 00:26:46,629
Where's Michael?

344
00:26:46,750 --> 00:26:48,555
Don't worry about Michael.

345
00:26:48,694 --> 00:26:50,577
He's not gonna find us.

346
00:26:52,115 --> 00:26:53,922
What do you want?

347
00:26:54,012 --> 00:26:56,436
Why don't you build
us a fire, John?

348
00:26:59,100 --> 00:27:02,053
Think it's time we
all had a talk.

349
00:27:12,606 --> 00:27:14,746
"Geronimo Jackson"?

350
00:27:15,883 --> 00:27:16,868
Huh.

351
00:27:18,901 --> 00:27:19,797
Whoo.

352
00:27:20,386 --> 00:27:22,360
As an expert in
all things musical,

353
00:27:22,818 --> 00:27:26,962
I never heard of these guys, shocking
as that may be. "Geronimo Jackson."

354
00:27:27,102 --> 00:27:30,086
This looks sweet.
Let's give her a rip.

355
00:27:30,612 --> 00:27:31,494
Yeah.

356
00:27:36,368 --> 00:27:39,635
So what do you think's the
story with that Libby chick?

357
00:27:39,742 --> 00:27:41,157
The story?

358
00:27:41,287 --> 00:27:43,218
She's kind of cute, right?

359
00:27:43,933 --> 00:27:45,019
You know, in a

360
00:27:45,113 --> 00:27:48,902
"I've been terrorized by the
others for 40 days" kind of way.

361
00:27:49,107 --> 00:27:51,733
Yeah, there is that.

362
00:27:56,015 --> 00:27:59,184
I think I have a
chance with her.

363
00:27:59,275 --> 00:28:01,575
I mean,
it's a classic desert island scenario.

364
00:28:01,601 --> 00:28:04,323
If I ever had a shot,
this is it.

365
00:28:08,150 --> 00:28:10,784
You  think Claire's
missed me yet?

366
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:14,532
Dude, it's been a day.

367
00:28:23,598 --> 00:28:26,041
This music is quite depressing.

368
00:28:26,162 --> 00:28:29,589
We can change it, dude.
You ever hear of Geronimo Jackson?

369
00:28:29,728 --> 00:28:32,334
I'm afraid not.
Where's Jack and Locke?

370
00:28:32,487 --> 00:28:34,127
Oh, they went after Michael.

371
00:28:34,829 --> 00:28:37,609
Michael? Yeah,
he's run after Walt again.

372
00:28:37,683 --> 00:28:39,532
Everyone's gone to
bring him back.

373
00:28:39,694 --> 00:28:40,977
Who's everyone?

374
00:28:41,088 --> 00:28:44,087
Everyone-- Jack, Sawyer, Locke.

375
00:28:44,180 --> 00:28:45,899
Oh, and Kate.

376
00:28:50,644 --> 00:28:55,498
Just sit down, Jack.
Nobody gonna hurt you. I come in peace.

377
00:28:55,888 --> 00:28:57,982
How do you know our names?

378
00:28:58,412 --> 00:28:59,915
You took Walt.

379
00:29:01,420 --> 00:29:03,183
Walt's fine.

380
00:29:03,399 --> 00:29:05,879
He's a very special boy.

381
00:29:06,037 --> 00:29:09,654
Look, you said you
wanted to talk. Talk.

382
00:29:10,142 --> 00:29:13,204
Let me ask you this--
how long you been here on the island?

383
00:29:14,548 --> 00:29:15,762
50 days.

384
00:29:16,034 --> 00:29:20,196
Ooh, 50 days.
That's, what, almost two whole months.

385
00:29:21,579 --> 00:29:26,012
Tell me, you go over a man's
house for the first time,

386
00:29:26,570 --> 00:29:29,552
do you take off your shoes?

387
00:29:29,654 --> 00:29:32,291
Do you put your feet up
on his coffee table?

388
00:29:33,021 --> 00:29:36,751
Do you walk in the kitchen and eat
food that doesn't belong to you,

389
00:29:36,911 --> 00:29:40,149
open the door to rooms you
got no business opening?

390
00:29:42,729 --> 00:29:46,847
You know, somebody a whole lot smarter
than anybody here once said that,

391
00:29:46,926 --> 00:29:54,102
"since the dawn of our species,
man has been blessed with curiosity."

392
00:29:54,301 --> 00:29:58,178
You know the other one about curiosity,
don't you, Jack?

393
00:30:00,824 --> 00:30:03,391
This is not your island.

394
00:30:03,578 --> 00:30:05,840
This is our island.

395
00:30:05,952 --> 00:30:08,422
And the only reason
you're living on it

396
00:30:08,597 --> 00:30:11,431
is 'cause we let
you live on it.

397
00:30:15,809 --> 00:30:17,326
I don't believe you.

398
00:30:19,521 --> 00:30:21,043
You don't believe what?

399
00:30:21,225 --> 00:30:24,913
I think you've got one
guy up there with a gun.

400
00:30:25,030 --> 00:30:28,181
I think there's more of
us than there are of you.

401
00:30:28,358 --> 00:30:30,769
I think if you had
any real strength,

402
00:30:30,876 --> 00:30:33,515
you wouldn't have
had to send a spy.

403
00:30:34,704 --> 00:30:36,610
Ethan.

404
00:30:40,810 --> 00:30:43,404
That's an interesting theory.

405
00:30:44,040 --> 00:30:45,559
Light 'em up!

406
00:30:50,502 --> 00:30:52,761
We got a
misunderstanding, Jack...

407
00:30:52,852 --> 00:30:55,231
your people, my people.

408
00:30:55,312 --> 00:30:57,343
So listen carefully.

409
00:30:57,491 --> 00:31:00,545
Right here there's a line.

410
00:31:01,134 --> 00:31:05,713
You cross that line,
we go from misunderstanding to...

411
00:31:05,800 --> 00:31:07,237
something else.

412
00:31:08,903 --> 00:31:13,921
Now give me your weapons, turn around.
Go home.

413
00:31:14,281 --> 00:31:15,703
No.

414
00:31:16,823 --> 00:31:19,009
- Jack, maybe--
- No!

415
00:31:21,767 --> 00:31:24,631
I hoped it wouldn't
come to this.

416
00:31:24,713 --> 00:31:26,701
Bring her out, Alex!

417
00:31:32,222 --> 00:31:34,472
She was following you.

418
00:31:34,644 --> 00:31:37,756
Like I said-- curiosity.

419
00:31:41,836 --> 00:31:43,278
Don't.

420
00:31:46,430 --> 00:31:50,229
Jack, the decision you gotta
make right now is this--

421
00:31:51,061 --> 00:31:55,959
Can you live with the fact that I shot
this woman right in front of you...

422
00:31:56,486 --> 00:32:01,492
When you could have saved her
life by giving up and going home?

423
00:32:02,402 --> 00:32:06,729
Now you gonna give me your guns,
turn around and walk away.

424
00:32:07,099 --> 00:32:09,702
It's your call, Jack.

425
00:32:10,326 --> 00:32:12,421
If you touched a hair
on her head, I'll--

426
00:32:12,436 --> 00:32:13,387
Shut up!

427
00:32:16,878 --> 00:32:19,332
I'm gonna count to three.

428
00:32:20,470 --> 00:32:21,606
One.

429
00:32:25,506 --> 00:32:26,696
two.

430
00:32:28,558 --> 00:32:29,786
Stop.

431
00:32:51,151 --> 00:32:52,589
Now them.

432
00:32:59,510 --> 00:33:01,331
Give me the other one, too.

433
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:23,756
You and me ain't done, Zeke.

434
00:33:55,537 --> 00:33:57,270
Jack, I...

435
00:33:59,283 --> 00:34:05,134
- You all right?
- Yeah.

436
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:24,390
*What are you you
doing out here alone?

437
00:34:25,251 --> 00:34:27,055
*I couldn't sleep.

438
00:34:28,736 --> 00:34:30,637
*Are they back?

439
00:34:30,883 --> 00:34:31,892
*Not yet.

440
00:34:36,612 --> 00:34:37,670
*Honey...

441
00:34:39,554 --> 00:34:43,092
*I don't like being
told what to do.

442
00:34:45,690 --> 00:34:50,720
*Being told what to do was
my life for four years...

443
00:34:52,917 --> 00:34:56,293
*I didn't like it much either.

444
00:35:00,082 --> 00:35:01,537
*Right.

445
00:35:03,373 --> 00:35:06,476
*I don't suppose you did.

446
00:35:37,693 --> 00:35:39,882
I was just trying
to help, Jack.

447
00:35:40,299 --> 00:35:43,019
When you told me not to go,
I just...

448
00:35:44,180 --> 00:35:46,171
I made a mistake.

449
00:35:48,181 --> 00:35:52,919
Hey. Could you just talk
to me for a second?

450
00:35:57,135 --> 00:35:58,456
I'm sorry.

451
00:36:00,574 --> 00:36:01,947
Yeah.

452
00:36:03,032 --> 00:36:04,887
I'm sorry, too.

453
00:36:23,816 --> 00:36:25,715
- Hey.
- Hey.

454
00:36:25,875 --> 00:36:27,393
How did it go?

455
00:36:29,170 --> 00:36:31,112
He died.

456
00:36:32,589 --> 00:36:34,017
I'm sorry.

457
00:36:34,340 --> 00:36:36,991
Yeah. Me too.

458
00:36:38,215 --> 00:36:41,052
- Who was over?
- My mom.

459
00:36:41,717 --> 00:36:44,245
Her bridge game okay?

460
00:36:44,805 --> 00:36:47,238
Oh, yeah. She's on a streak.

461
00:36:48,048 --> 00:36:50,049
Did you-- did you eat?

462
00:36:50,228 --> 00:36:52,761
Yeah. No, I--it's...

463
00:36:53,356 --> 00:36:55,581
it's late. I'm fine.

464
00:37:03,012 --> 00:37:04,342
You don't have to do that.

465
00:37:04,524 --> 00:37:08,095
It's therapeutic.
Cheaper than a shrink.

466
00:37:18,986 --> 00:37:21,515
How'd the daughter take it?

467
00:37:22,487 --> 00:37:24,440
What's her name-- Gabriela?

468
00:37:25,187 --> 00:37:26,638
She kissed me.

469
00:37:31,272 --> 00:37:33,117
Yeah, she...

470
00:37:34,297 --> 00:37:37,213
she kissed me, and...

471
00:37:37,894 --> 00:37:39,347
I kissed her back.

472
00:37:40,796 --> 00:37:46,303
I... I don't know.
I don't know how it happened. I just...

473
00:37:47,791 --> 00:37:49,793
I made a mistake.

474
00:37:50,454 --> 00:37:52,894
I made a mistake,
and this is my fault.

475
00:37:53,056 --> 00:37:54,730
It's my fault that you and me--

476
00:37:55,831 --> 00:37:59,820
I haven't been here, Sarah.
I mean...

477
00:38:01,566 --> 00:38:04,004
We don't even talk anymore.

478
00:38:05,777 --> 00:38:08,393
I hate what's
happening to us, and

479
00:38:08,500 --> 00:38:10,896
I promise you that things
are gonna be different.

480
00:38:10,926 --> 00:38:13,279
I'm gonna--
I'm gonna work less.

481
00:38:13,539 --> 00:38:15,761
I'm gonna be here for you.

482
00:38:16,227 --> 00:38:18,937
Okay? I'm gonna fix this. We're
gonna go back to the way things were.

483
00:38:18,967 --> 00:38:21,965
I'm gonna fix this.
I'm gonna fix this.

484
00:38:30,145 --> 00:38:30,862
Jack.

485
00:38:32,247 --> 00:38:33,175
Jack...

486
00:38:39,459 --> 00:38:45,370
- I'm leaving you.
- What?

487
00:38:47,005 --> 00:38:48,386
I was already leaving you.

488
00:38:48,565 --> 00:38:51,901
That's why my mother was here.
She was helping me pack.

489
00:39:06,856 --> 00:39:11,167
I've been seeing someone...

490
00:39:16,250 --> 00:39:18,625
someone else.

491
00:39:22,075 --> 00:39:23,853
I have to...

492
00:39:24,886 --> 00:39:26,656
I can't stay.

493
00:39:29,353 --> 00:39:31,017
Sarah...

494
00:39:31,509 --> 00:39:32,636
You...

495
00:39:35,588 --> 00:39:40,979
you will always need
something to fix.

496
00:39:44,813 --> 00:39:46,025
Good-bye.

497
00:40:09,431 --> 00:40:10,541
See you, James.

498
00:40:15,451 --> 00:40:17,647
Don't beat yourself
up, Freckles.

499
00:40:18,141 --> 00:40:21,441
If he'd told me to stay behind,
I'd have done the same damn thing.

500
00:40:26,668 --> 00:40:28,115
Oh. Hello.

501
00:40:28,322 --> 00:40:29,515
What's the matter?

502
00:40:29,692 --> 00:40:31,618
What's the matter with
your little foot?

503
00:40:31,648 --> 00:40:33,016
Hi. Hi!

504
00:40:33,195 --> 00:40:34,768
Who's that?

505
00:40:36,063 --> 00:40:38,268
You don't like
your uncle Johnny?

506
00:40:39,277 --> 00:40:42,277
What is he doing to your toy?

507
00:40:42,561 --> 00:40:44,027
What is he doing?

508
00:40:48,014 --> 00:40:50,006
Hey, go away.

509
00:40:50,587 --> 00:40:53,407
I barely have enough
food to feed myself.

510
00:40:53,921 --> 00:40:56,195
Here. Get that. Go!

511
00:40:58,350 --> 00:41:00,377
I see you found a new friend.

512
00:41:01,967 --> 00:41:03,174
Progress.

513
00:41:09,475 --> 00:41:12,224
Hear you were out
lookin' for Michael.

514
00:41:14,084 --> 00:41:15,411
Yeah.

515
00:41:18,192 --> 00:41:20,786
He ran off looking
for his kid again?

516
00:41:29,714 --> 00:41:32,435
Not much you can do
about that then.

517
00:41:36,358 --> 00:41:39,203
Is it true that you
killed one of them?

518
00:41:40,137 --> 00:41:42,006
One of who?

519
00:41:42,909 --> 00:41:43,989
Them.

520
00:41:49,666 --> 00:41:52,625
Sayid tells me
that you're a cop.

521
00:41:55,140 --> 00:41:57,227
I was a cop.

522
00:41:58,137 --> 00:42:00,072
Can I ask you something?

523
00:42:00,672 --> 00:42:01,840
Shoot.

524
00:42:04,370 --> 00:42:07,885
How long do you think it
